definition.value: An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of L-glutamic acid, having anionic carboxy groups and a cationic amino group
An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of D-glutamic acid, having anionic carboxy groups and a cationic amino group
A dicarboxylic acid dianion that is the conjugate base of glutamate(1-).
An L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the dianion obtained by the deprotonation of the both the carboxy groups of L-glutamic acid.
A pentacyclic triterpenoid that is bayogenin substituted at the O-3 position by a cellobiosyl residue.
An aspartate(1-) that is the conjugate base of D-aspartic acid.
An aspartate(1-) that is the  conjugate base of L-aspartic acid.
An aspartate(2-) that is the conjugate base of  L-aspartate(1-).
An aspartate(2-) that is the conjugate base of D-aspartate(1-).
A C4-dicarboxylate that is the dianion obtained by the deprotonation of both the carboxy groups of aspartic acid.
A serine residue that has L configuration.
A trimeric cyclodepsipeptide composed from alternating methylphenylalanyl and hydroxyvaleryl residues.
A 17alpha-hydroxy steroid that is prednisolone in which the hydrogens at the 9alpha and 16beta positions are substituted by a chlorine and a methyl group, respectively.
A steroid ester comprising beclomethasone having propionyl groups at the 17- and 21-positions.
A member of the class of cinnamates that is the conjugate base of trans-sinapic acid.
